  <brief_title>A Comparison of the Safety and Effectiveness of Fluconazole or Clotrimazole in the Treatment of Fungal Infections of the Mouth and Throat in Patients With AIDS</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Randomized Multicenter Study of the Efficacy, Safety, and Toleration of Fluconazole or Clotrimazole Troches in the Treatment of Patients With Oropharyngeal Candidiasis in Association With the Acquired Immunodeficiency Syndrome</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Pfizer</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>NIH AIDS Clinical Trials Information Service</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To compare the efficacy, safety, and tolerance of fluconazole single daily capsule for 14
      days versus clotrimazole troche 5 x daily for 14 days in the treatment of oropharyngeal
      candidiasis in patients with AIDS.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
